events.name: ミノタウロス討伐　エリカ待機

parameters:
\n< Serena >Phew... We've arrived. This is the place, Erika-
sama!
\n< Serena >Erika-sama! Are you not here?

\n< Serena >...Hmm, I can't believe I said something so
pointless. If she's not here, there won't be a
response.
\n< Erika >You're not here.
\n< Serena >....
エリカ HK_PT01-1
エリカ HK_PT01-1

\n< Erika >Hmm, thank you for your hard work in transporting
the supplies. Is Serena-chan part of today's
supply unit?
\n< Erika >Oh, there you are.

\n< Erika >Hehe, you're still the same, huh? You look even
cuter after crawling around in the bushes all day.
\n< Serena >Erika-sama, you have quite the warrior spirit.

\n< Erika >That's right, that's right. I spent quite a bit of
money on this. It's my pride and joy!

\n< Serena >That outfit is the same as the other day... Ah,
come to think of it, I still haven't thanked you
for that time.
\n< Erika >Hm? Did something happen?

\n< Serena >It was during the goblin incident. If it weren't
for you, I would have been in a dangerous
situation.
\n< Serena >Thank you again, Erika-sama.
\n< Erika >Ehh? Well... hehe...!
\n< Serena >What is it?

\n< Erika >Ahh, I don't really want to be thanked face-to-
face.

\n< Erika >Hehe, I'm getting embarrassed. Ehehe. My neck is
starting to itch for some reason.
\n< Serena >...Is that how it is...?

\n< Serena >Erika-sama, you truly have the spirit of a
warrior.
\n< Erika >Oh? Cool?
\n< Serena >You've changed quite a bit.

\n< Serena >You always dress indecently in town, so I wonder
if you'll be the same in the forest.
\n< Erika >Hehehe... Huh? Did you just say indecent?

\n< Erika >Well, even though I'm me, I'll make sure to
prepare my equipment properly in the middle of the
forest.

\n< Erika >Of course, not only for battles but also for
trekking through the bushes, it's not like I can
do it with my bare skin exposed.
\n< Serena >Are those horns also for bushwhacking?

\n< Erika >Well! I mean, it's not like it's just for
intimidation or design, it's not all about
practicality either, you know.

\n< Serena >Sigh... I thought you would have a serious
expression for once... but you never change.
\n< Erika >They say laughter is the best friend in life.
\n< Serena >Huh? Whose words are those?
\n< Erika >I-
\n< Serena >...I see...
\n< Erika >So, did you bring the food and supplies?
\n< Serena >It's sudden, isn't it...
\n< Serena >Here it is.
\n< Erika >Yappy! Here it is! Food, too.
\n< Serena >...? What is it? A metal ball...?
\n< Erika >Hmm? Ti-ti-ti... it's a little different...
\n< Erika >This is a grenade.

\n< Erika >Inside this metal ball, there's a bunch of
gunpowder and magic. It's the latest military
weapon, you know.

\n< Erika >Well, to be precise, it's the compact version.
With this, I'll blow away that Minotaur bastard.

\n< Erika >It was a pain in the ass to procure it
individually... It cost money and I had to use
connections... Finally, it arrived.

\n< Serena >Is the Minotaur monster really such a formidable
opponent that we need military-grade weapons like
this?

\n< Erika >Well... If you're prepared, you have nothing to
worry about, right?

\n< Erika >After all, it's a big shot. I have to keep one
secret weapon up my sleeve.

\n< Erika >Well, rather than talking about dangerous things
like that... I want to talk about food now.

\n< Erika >I miscalculated. I've been skipping meals since
yesterday. I've been nibbling on unknown mushrooms
and starving myself.
\n< Serena >...You've really gone too far, haven't you...

\n< Erika >Mmm, it smells, it smells. The delicious aroma of
freshly baked bread is wafting from around here.

\n< Erika >Alrighty! Then, how about having lunchtime
together with Serena today!

\n< Serena >I have no idea what's good anymore. I'm planning
to go home.
\n< Serena >If we hurry now, we can return to town by midday.

\n< Serena >I want to finish one more task by the end of
today.
\n< Erika >Ehh... Big sis is disappointed...

\n< Erika >Well, if that's the case, there's a shortcut. I'll
guide you.
\n< Serena >Hmmm? That would be helpful.
\n< Erika >Hey, wanna chat along the way?

\n< Serena >So that's your intention... Well, if it's just
that, I don't mind.
